<appendix id="app.admin.docupdates">
 <title>Documentation Updates</title>
 <para>
  This chapter lists content changes for this document since the release of
  &productnamereg; 11 SP3.
 </para>
 <para>
  This manual was updated on the following dates:
 </para>
<!--list of xrefs, latest date sorted upmost-->
 <itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
   <para>
    <xref linkend="sec.admin.docupdates.sle12_ga" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
   </para>
  </listitem>
 </itemizedlist>
<!-- 

fs 2014-01-31: Fix for FATE #316691: provide nouveau driver, unsupported

-->

 <sect1 id="sec.admin.docupdates.sle12_ga">
  <title>September XX, 2014 (Initial Release of &productname; 12)</title>

  <para/>

  <variablelist>
   <!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
   <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" href="common_docupdates_general_i.xml"/>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
    <!-- Gathering System Information for Support -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.adm.support"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added sentence about <command>hostinfo</command> when logging in
	(<ulink url="http://fate.suse.com/315869"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added new sections <xref linkend="sec.admsupport.hostinfo"
	xrefstyle="select:title"/>, <xref linkend="sec.admsupport.sca"
	xrefstyle="select:title"/>, and <xref linkend="sec.admsupport.kernel"
	xrefstyle="select:title"/> (<ulink
	url="https://fate.suse.com/315869"/>, <ulink
	url="https://fate.suse.com/315699"/>, <ulink
	url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=871928"/>, and <ulink
	url="https://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=869159"/>).
	Restructured chapter.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!--  Remote Access with VNC -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.vnc"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	default vnc viewer is now <systemitem
	class="resource">tigervnc</systemitem>
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Corrections on windowmanger startup in persistent VNC sessions
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- Booting a Linux System -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.boot"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Significantly shortened the chapter, because System V init has been
	replaced by systemd. systemd is now described in a separate chapter:
	<xref linkend="cha.systemd"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- The systemd daemon -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.systemd"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added a new chapter on systemd and the &yast; &ycc_runlevel;.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- The Boot Loader GRUB 2 -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.grub2"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Replaced the GRUB legacy documentation with a new chapter on &grub;.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- The X Window System -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.x11"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Updated the chapter to reflect dynamic configuration during each
	start-up.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- SLP -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.slp" os="sles"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Re-wrote chapter to provide significantly more information on the
	<command>slptool</command> command. 
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- Sharing File Systems with NFS -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.nfs"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Configuring NFSv4 shares is now mostly similar to NFSv3,
	especially the previously required bind mount setting is now
	deprecated (<ulink url="http://fate.suse.com/315589"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="osuse;sles">
       <para>
        Mounting NFS volumes locally on the exporting server is not
        supported.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem os="sled">
       <para>
        Removed section about NFS server configuration.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- On-Demand Mounting with Autofs -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.autofs"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added a chapter on AutoFS.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry os="sles">
    <!-- The Apache HTTP Server -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.apache2"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Removed references to mono and mod_mono as it was removed from the
	distribution.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the chapter to Apache version 2.4 (<ulink
        url="http://fate.suse.com/316067"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Removed deprecated directive <literal>NameVirtualHost</literal>
        and updated <xref linkend="sec.apache2.configuration.manually.vhost"/>
        accordingly.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Updated <literal>Order</literal>, <literal>Allow</literal>, and
	<literal>Deny</literal> directives with standard
	<literal>Require</literal>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Removed virtual "Snake Oil" company from <xref
         linkend="sec.apache2.ssl"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <!-- Common Problems and Their Solutions -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.trouble"/></term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added new section <xref linkend="sec.trouble.boot.btrfs"
	xrefstyle="select:title"/> (<ulink url="http://fate.suse.com/308679"/>
	and <ulink url="http://fate.suse.com/315126"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Added new section <xref linkend="sec.trouble.boot.btrfs"
	xrefstyle="select:title"/> (<ulink url="http://fate.suse.com/308679"/>
	and <ulink url="http://fate.suse.com/315126"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
	Removed section about deprecated &yast; Repair module (<ulink
        url="http://fate.suse.com/308679"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
</appendix>
